HEADWORD: Krameria
<hw>Kra*me"ri*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <ety>[NL. So
called after the German botanists, <person>J. G. H. Kramer</person> &
<person>W. H. <etsep>Kramer</etsep></person>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A genus of spreading shrubs with many stems, from one species of
which (<spn>Krameria triandra</spn>), found in <country>Peru</country>,
rhatany root, used as a medicine, is obtained.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

